				open your control panel and then click on Programs<br />
				*do not click on Uninstall a program*
				</p>
				
				<img src="img/control_panel.jpg" width="800">
				
				<p>Click the java icon</p>
				<img src="img/control_panel_prog.jpg" width="800">
				
				<p>Click on the Security Tab</p>
				<img src="img/java_control_panel.jpg" width="800">
				
				<p>Click the Edit Site List button</p>
				<img src="img/security.jpg" width="800">
				
				<p>Click on the add button</p>
				<img src="img/security_except.jpg" width="800">
				
				<p>Copy the url<br />
				http://javaapplet-mikegames.rhcloud.com/javaapplet/index.jsp
				</p>
				
				<img src="img/highlight_url.jpg" width="800">
				
				<p>Paste it in the Exception Site List location</p>
				<img src="img/security_add.jpg" width="800">	
							
				<p>Click OK</p>
				<img src="img/security_ok.jpg" width="800">
				
				<p>Click Continue</p>
				<img src="img/security_warning.jpg" width="800">
	
				<p>Close and restart the web browser<br/>
					When Security Warning pops up click Run 
				</p>
								
				<img src="img/run_app.jpg" width="800">

				<p>
					You should see something like this<br />
					Double click on the inside to set focus on the applet
